Jan 18 2009 	Excellent Business Hotel	I stayed at the Grand Hyatt in Dubai for two weeks in November 2008. Reason was a business trip. We chose the Hyatt as my company has relocated to nearby Health Care City.The hotel is about 10-15 minutes drive from the Airport. Airport transfer are being conducted in a BMW 7 series, by very professional and curteous drivers. Once arrived at the hotel, check in was swift and efficient. We were staying at the Grand Club. The Grand Club Lounge is very big, actually two lounges are existing. The Lounge is open 24 hours and you can always have soft drinks for free which is very nice. A good espresso machine where you can have good espressos/capuccinos is also available 24 hours.The buffet breakfast at the lounge is exclusively continental, you cannot have any egg dishes which is a bit disappointing. The fresh juices they serve are to die for.During the day there is always something small to nibble, before in the evening there is the regular cocktail/hors d'oeuvres hours which extens from 6 - 9 Pm which is nice so you can still relax there after a longer day with a glass of wine e.g. The evening spread for the hors d'oeuvres is ok, but the same as the breakfast a little bit disappointing.The room is spacious and very well maintained/ modern. The entertainment system is top notch, as the TV is from B&amp;O. Selection of channels is great, even a regular German channel (ZDF) was included, which was for me, being a German, great. But also plenty of free movie channels, news channels in all languages were available. The bed is very comfortable and there is ample closet space through a nice walk in closet. Best feature of the room is the bath, whihc is extremely spacious with a separate shower stall which is very spacious too. Housekeeping service is twice a day and very efficient/effective.Restaurant Choice is very good at this hotel. There is a italian, steakhouse, singaporean, sushi, southeast-asian, lebanese/arab and an indian restaurant. My favorite was the indian restaurant which served indian food in a very nice setting and innovative and was surprisingly moderately priced.There is also moevenpick style restaurant which also is very convienent if you want to grab something very fast. Hotel has all the other facilities such as spa, hairdresser, a great pool area, atm machine and other shops.There are also several bars and a night club. the night club MIX was only open on the weekend unfortunately.The only drawback is that the hotel is quite isolated and it takes some time to go to the center of Dubai, nevertheless nearby Al Wafi Mall makes up for some shopping alternatives.Hotel can get quite expensive depending on the season, we paid around 500 USD a night, which i personally quite pricey, but i guess this is what you pay for a top notch hotel in Dubai.Overall the excellent business hotel, to which i will definitely return.	
Jan 18 2009 	Nice hotel in a good location	The Grand Hyatt is a good hotel in a great location. Located next to Wafi mall, it is well located for most things in Deira and it’s easy to get to Jumeirah (outside of peak traffic times) from here. We stayed in a grand club room which gave us access to the private lounge including transfers to/from the airport, breakfast, drinks, canapés, access to the business centre etc and is definitely worth paying the extra cost.Food in the lounge lacked variety but was tasty and while the choice of non-alcoholic drinks was limited they did have a good selection of fruit juice. Alcoholic drinks were available between 6-9pm which definitely makes it worth paying the extra room cost as alcohol in Dubai is expensive.Our room on the 11th floor had amazing views of the creek and city. The room was large, light and airy, but lacked things that you would normally find such as an iron or stationary. The bed was extremely big, but a little too hard for us. The bath room was large, with a big and powerful shower, a small separate bath and the toilet was hidden away behind a frosted glass door. Annoyingly the hairdryer wasn’t very good, so if like me you like to dry your hair in 2 minutes, bring your own. The quality of food at the hotel is mixed. We had room service and ate at Andiamo’s and Sushi which were all excellent. But unfortunately the pool bar/restaurant was of poor quality and taste.The hotel pool is large, but there was a lot of maintenance work going on around the pool while people were in it which was a little disconcerting. As the pool is so big it’s a shame that there is no in-pool bar, particularly as the pool-side service is very slow. However the pool is temperature controlled so it was nice to be able to have a swim despite it feeling a little cold in the wind.Unfortunately we did have one argument with the hotel who tried to impose a compulsory charge on us for the New Year’s Eve celebrations. We were not told about the charge when we confirmed our reservation nor upon checking in, so we were rather angry when a rude member of staff phoned us in our room to say that the charge was being applied and then hung up the phone. We spoke to the manager Ashwin about this who agreed that his staff were sometimes a little abrupt and apologised about not telling us about the charge in advance. He was very courteous and explained the charge covered unlimited alcoholic drinks, a laser show and an indoor fireworks display; and he then gave us time to go away and think about whether or not we would like to be involved in the celebrations. While wondering around the hotel and discussing whether or not to go to the Grand Hyatt party, the events people at the hotel were practicing the laser show and fireworks in the lobby and based on what we saw we decided that it was not worth was 1200 AED to join in the celebrations – it would have been cheaper to clear out the minibar instead.Ashwin was very understanding and let us off the charge. As it turned out celebrations were cancelled by Sheikh Mohammad and the hotel was only allowed to do something low key, but the hotel still didn’t let guests off the charge, they had to pay irrespective.We chose the Grand Hyatt as my husband had been here on business. The hotel is good considering the number of rooms that it manages, but it lacks the magic that you find in many of Dubai’s other hotels. But is makes a good base if it’s your first time or if you don’t know Dubai very well. But if you are looking for some of Dubai’s charm, you won’t find it here.	
