Dec 22 2008 	Perfect resort hotel (without beach 	I stay at Grand Hyatt Dubai once a year... and after 3 years still find it a nice hotel to spend a few relaxing nights. It's a big hotel but don't let the +700 rooms withold you of staying here ! Once in the hotel you never get the impression that it's crowded, the lobby is big enough - still impressive the 3 enormous boat keels that hang in the lobby - the staff take their time to welcome you and guarantee a quick and hassle free check-in. The rooms are nice and big with of course all the usual amenities of a 5* hotel (TV, internet, safe, bathrobe, huge soft fluffy towels...). Rooms are carpeted, bathroom has tiles.Nice clean marble bathroom with shower (no bath), separate wc and bidet. However the little trays with the bathroom amenities are getting a little worn out. There are quite some restaurants here and my favourite still is &quot;The Peppercrab&quot;; an asian fusion cuisine but oh so lovely and tasty presented !! For cheap &amp; quick try &quot;The Marketplace&quot;, where also breakfast is served. You can get a decent meal for around 25 Euro per person, it's divided into 3 open kitchens where you will find tasty asian, indian and italian dishes. The hotel has a huge garden with swimming pool &amp; poolbar, covered childrens pool, Spa, jogging track and other sports facilities. I fell asleep by the poolside one afternoon and when I woke up the poolbar was just closing but the waiter still came over and asked me if I wanted to order drinks. I find this hotel a perfect resort hotel, the only thing it doesn't have is a beach &amp; seaview. But who needs this with Wafi Shopping center &amp; cinema's only 5 min. away on foot (yes you can walk to Wafi).I recommend this hotel for business purpose (consider bringing your partner/ children along) and normal tourists too.	
