Oct 7 2008 	Great service at the Hyatt	We spent 3 nights here at the beginnng of October. We arrived very early in the morning 7.30am and they gave us a room immediately. Room was great, large, bright, excellent facilities and views. We had booked on a B&amp;B basis and even though we weren't entitled to breakfast on our first day the reception staff suggested we visited the 14th floor where there was an excellent buffet breakfast - no eggs and bacon but meats, smoked salmon, bread, pastries etc. with more great views - all free!Room was cleaned every time we were out and water and fruit replenished. The atrium was forested with real trees and pools with koi.Whenever we asked for something it was done promptly and with a smile. At one point we were in the lobby waiting to speak to someone about booking a trip - it was very busy and all the staff were busy but a gentleman doing something on the other side of the lobby spotted that we had been waiting about 30 seconds and came to help and we were sorted out immediately.The pool area was great, people promptly helped with towels, moving parasols etc. The people sorting out taxis were also efficient. We visited quite a few other hotels in Dubai during our stay for drinks and food and the service at the Hyatt outshone them all.Overall the place was impeccable and the staff were the cherry on the cake.	
Oct 6 2008 	Excellent once again	We have just returned from another wonderful stay at the Grand Hyatt, in Dubai. This was our 3rd stay at the hotel, which we initially booked for 6 nights, but enjoyed it so much, we extended it for a further 2 nights, mid-stay.Flew overnight, from Heathrow, on Emirates and arrived at the hotel at 8am.Although we were not entitled to a room until 3pm, the hotel was not full and we went through the usual check-in procedure, you are in a standard city view room, would you like to pay to upgrade to a city view room? (we declined), swipe the credit card and they handed us our key. As we walked away to go to our room, we were called back. One more thing, Mr &amp; Mrs Fisher, sadly our swimming pool is out of use and we wish to make available to you, the facilities at our sister hotels the Park Hyatt and Hyatt Regency. Again we declined, saying that we didn’t want to spend all day going backwards and forwards between hotels. We asked to see the manager, who was of course, unavailable. We said that we would see him later. I was not happy about this situation, at all. I had been in daily e-mail contact with the hotel asking various things and this had not been mentioned once.We went to the room and unpacked and headed to the pool to see what was going on. The 2 children’s pools were OK and lots of adults were just hanging around there and sitting in the water to cool off, when necessary. The main pool had been completely drained and was being re-tiled and repaired / cleaned, where necessary. Apparently a water inlet pipe had burst underground and had pumped dirty water into the pool meaning it had to be drained, cleaned and re-filled. Whilst it was empty it made sense to make any required repairs. Maybe this was true, but it was a bit of a coincidence that it was coming to the end of Ramadan and the hotel was only half full.Anyway, the manager visited our room that evening and we made the point that to us, as tourists, the pool was the hotels biggest selling point and is what makes it in our opinion the best hotel in the city. The manager offered us complimentary dinners (Manhattan Grill Steakhouse and Peppercrab Seafood) for the days that we would be without a pool, we agreed that a fixed amount of credit be set against our account, per day. Personally, we prefer to eat out and about and this meant we weren’t tied to spending it on specific nights, in specific places.The main pool returned to full use on our third day and we got on with enjoying our holiday. We enjoyed it so much, that we asked what our credit would by us in terms of extra nights. The manager agreed that if we paid a discounted rate for one extra night, they would use our credit to give us a 2nd extra night and then upgrade us “free” for the rest of our stay to Grand Club. We had to pay extra to Emirates to change the date of our return flight, but the savings on our bar bill, during the 6pm-9pm cocktail hour probably paid for that, anyway!!We ate out at Thai Chi (excellent, as always) and Carters at Wafi City. We did suffer at Carters, on the night we had pre-dinner drinks there before going into Thai Chi. They have a 6pm – 8pm Happy Hour, where drinks prices are reduced. We ordered our last round of drinks at 7.50 and the bar man seemed to be unusually slow in pouring them and then when I asked to pay the bill, he again seemed to be taking as long as he could. He passed me the bill and all of the drinks were full-price. I asked what happened to Happy Hour and he pointed out that the bill was printed at 8.01pm. Sharp practice, but the manager did his job and sorted it out, although i did have to threaten to cancel our dinner reservation there for the following night. When we did return the next day, the service was excellent.These incidents are excellent examples of the way things should be handled and after hearing some of the horror stories coming out of the Atlantis opening week, these are the reasons that we shall return to Grand Hyatt, Dubai, very soon.	
