Oct 1 2008 	The most luxurious room i've ever had!	I had 4 nights here on a stopover enroute back to Australia. (Late Aug/Early Sept) Decided to treat myself and ended up here at the Hyatt!The hotel organised a limo to pick me up from the airport, It was a nice little BMW with Bar Fridge, But since the hotel is only a 10 min drive from the airport i didnt get to enjoy it for too long!Once i arrived the porter took my bag and i proceeded to the Check In Desk. The gentleman who checked me in was very friendly (I think he was turkish) and I was issued a room on the 9th floor and wow...... I asked for the basic room but it felt more like a suite and i ended up having a creek view despite not thinking i was getting one!The bed was SO comfortable and the walls were soundproofed really well! The Shower and Bath were fitted with gold fixtures and had a very generous supply of tolietries! The Plasma tv had about 50 channels with about 20 english and the rest a combination of Arabic, Hindu, and even russian!There was a fully stocked Mini Bar (Which was great considering it was going into Ramadan) and an air conditioning unit which was able to be controlled. And believe me in Dubai you'll want the Air Conditioner on 24/7!The Outdoor Pool is just amazing! It really is as huge as it is portrayed but they close it at 8pm! However the Indoor Pool and spa which are smaller but nice in their own degree are open until 11pm! As i was there during the start of ramadan the hotel kept around 2 restaurants open each day for westerners, I did try the Market Cafe one night for dinner, They give you a card and once in the buffet as you choose what you want you get the server to swipe it and at the end of your meal you can choose to pay it there and then or add to your hotel bill.I booked the City tour and Desert Safari through Orient Tours, I highly recommend them! I also saw a lot of Arabian Adventures tour buses around!Taxi's are plentiful and the guys outside would always call you one immediately. It costs around 5 dirham to get to Wafi Mall, or 35 Dirham to get to Mall of the Emirates (Ski Dubai), 40 Dirham to Jumeirah Beach. The taxi's are all clean and brand new Toyota Camry's! And most importantly air conditioned!The only thing i can fault this hotel on is i found the staff a little too intrusive at times, Relaxing by the pool they would constantly appear and try and get you things, Housekeeping were constantly up and down the halls cleaning rooms (Take note: leave your Do not Disturb Switch on or else you could get knocks on the door 3 or 4 times).And i felt they were constantly wanting tips! I'd be happy to stay here again, But next time i think i'll try one of the Jumeirah Beach hotels!	
