Mar 25 2008 	Return visit just as good	I previously wrote a very favourable review for this hotel in June 2006 and I can confirm that nothing has changed in the almost 2 years since we visited it previously. The level of service is still as high and the property itself is still maintained to a very high standard.RoomsWe stayed in a Club Creekview Room and on initial check in they did not have our request of a high room with no smoking. Had to take a smoking room for the first evening and they do really smell of smoke! We were moved without any problem the next morning to a very nice room (1041) on the 10th floor and it had additional floor space as it was on the end of the corridor.The room is spacious with again the walk in wardrobe to store all your shopping!!The standard of cleaning is very high with morning cleaning and evening turndown. Nothing to complain about on this front.Food/LoungeWe used the lounge area for breakfast each morning instead of the Market area - you can use either one. It was very quiet and peaceful up there on the 14th floor instead of the frenzied noise downstairs. The selection is only continental but this is all we wanted anyway so it suited our needs.In the evening drinks and canapes are served from 6-9pm so plenty of time to have a drink before dinner. Food is very good and if you are not too hungry you could easily eat there each evening and not bother with dinner. We noticed a lot of the business travellers doing this. Look out for Leo who serves you like a true professional and with a good personality.PoolThe pool area is enormous and for those who like space when swimming then this is ideal. The water is luke warm so easy to slip into when you are a bit hot from the sun. The standard of cleanliness is also very high and there is always a staff member available to move your bed or umbrella if they see you trying to do it yourself. The cucumber and cold towels still arrive each day.Water by the pool is not too expensive for a 5 star, just over €4 for a large bottle of perrier. We did not eat by the pool but the food looked delicious.Room Service was also reasonable for a 5 star and beautifully served in your room. GymWe used the gym most days and althought it is not an enormous facility there was never a problem using the equipment and the staff were always to hand to show you how to use the equipment.ShoppingThe shopping area beside the hotel &quot;the Wafi Centre&quot; is a lovely centre but very expensive, unless you normally shop in high end shops then don't think you will buy much here. We travelled in to the Deira City Centre mall which was only 14AED by taxi (about €2.50) the only problem is getting back, the queues for taxis can sometimes be up to an hour!! Be warned, leave before the centre closes if you can or go during the daytime.We also took a look into the new Raffles hotel, looked fantastic and the pool and gym area are nice too but quite small.All in all, can not fault the hotel, no niggles that we can think of. We had a brilliant 10 days and will definitely return.	
Mar 23 2008 	Huge hotel amazing pool area ok location	Just returned from 5 night stay at Grand Hyatt having been impressed by photos of the HUGE pool area and Vegas looking size hotel! 1st great surprise was the distance from the airport. Having just arrived from Kuala Lumpur where the taxi ride from airport to hotel was an hour we were shocked to come out the airport, join a motorway, cross a newly built bridge and then swing into the hotels impressive entrance! I thought you couldnt beat Vegas for hotel closeness!! It was 6am &amp; we'd requested an early check-in hoping maybe mid-day and we were met with an apology for the fact that our room wouldnt be ready until 7am! We were treated to a free drink in the grand lobby bar, had a quick look around at the excellent array of restaurants set among indoor plantation and flowing water (very american, very cool) &amp; then collected our room key (820) &amp; after a bit of messing around with the room key to work the lights (it goes in upside down?) we were blown away by the great size of the room, the his/hers sinks in the lovely bathroom, the 'walk-in' style wardrobe and a fantastic view of the city complete with soon to be biggest building in the world - Burj Dubai. The closest room to Wynn, Las Vegas I've stayed in. I'd emailed ahead to let them know it was our honeymoon and my wife's 30th and we were thrilled to wake up after our morning nap with a vase with 40 red roses in the room (if not a bit freaked out that someone had been in the room and walked passed us both asleep on the bed?!?!). That night we returned from a busy day at Wild Wadi &amp; Ski Dubai to find a bottle of Beaujolais, chocalates and dates in the room. Gobsmacked!! As if the flowers werent enough! If we werent sold before we were now.Pool area absolutely 100% perfect. Plenty of sunbeds in various areas so if you want to be away from the crowd you can. Great area for kids which was empty and we spent one p.m sunbathing there and were the only people there! Great staff around the pool as soon as you arrive they are helping you with towels and laying them out on. Steak sandwiches &amp; club sandwich gorgeous (approx £10 each) but the real winner was the cheese burger (same). Beer approx £5 but brought up in ice cold glass and worth every penny in the heat! Gym equipment topclass and very helpful advisors in there too. One corrected me on the bench press which I'd been doing very slightly wrong for 3 yrs without anyone in my gym mentioning it. Same guy then took time out to advice me on best routine which i scribbled down on paper and will be using for the next 3mths to check the results. Again its this 5* stuff that you stroll back to your sunbed really appreciating. Location could be its one and only downfall as we tended to be heading for the Jumeirah beach for a lot of things - Wild Wadi, Ski Dubai, Mall of Emirates, Burj al Arab &amp; a visit to the Buddha Bar restaurant in the Grosvenor House Hotel (DO NOT MISS THIS RESTAURANT/BAT - AMAZING!!). Whereas this end of Dubai we only needed for the Creek and the Gold Souks. That said the taxis are cheap (approx £8 for the 20-25 min ride to the Burj Al Arab area) and are all over the place and with the size of Dubai no matter where you are you need taxis between most places you are going anyway so it wasnt THAT much of a big deal and also there is a great restaurant/bar area in walking distance over by Wafi Mall (Planet Hollywood, Sevilles (spanish tapas) etc) and then theres the great rests in the hotel. We ate in the Italian one night which was fantastic. All in all great staff, big smiles everywhere, prompt efficient service, great pool, gym. I'd return to this one and recommend it to everyone, but I might check out the Jumeirah beach properties. Some hotels you can use their 'sister' hotel on the beach and if Hyaytt introduced this it'd be great. Hope this helps!	
