Dec 1 2007 	Grand Hyatt - Out of this world!	My husband and I stayed at the Grand Hyatt Dubai between the 23rd and 30th September ’07 and absolutely loved it! From the moment we arrived the staff could not have been more helpful or attentive, we had arrived on an overnight flight from London with Virgin Atlantic. Before we left we had been warned by Virgin that although we would be arriving at about 7.30am we wouldn’t be able to check in to our room until 3pm. However, when we arrived and asked if we could leave our bags somewhere, reception told us they could check us in right away.We were told the room would be ready in about 40 minutes and in the meantime, pointed us in the direction of the Market Café where breakfast is served. The staff were so apologetic about this delay – but for us it was incredible as we had not been expecting to check in for another 6 or 7 hours. The breakfasts at the Hyatt are out of this world – we had never seen so much food or food so fresh. There was every kind of breakfast imaginable – including a chocolate fountain! The Market Café is exactly as it sounds, set up as lots of different stalls with different themes. As it was Ramadan the café was screened off but remained open all day for food. The other restaurants were closed during the day but opened after sunset – although a word of warning, Anwar was closed our entire stay due to Ramadan.Our room was very generously sized – a Grand city view room which had an amazing view of Dubai’s skyline. It was clean and had every amenity you could wish for. A very well stocked mini-bar, TV with lots of cable channels and an exquisite crystal glass set should we wish to enjoy a tipple. The walk in wardrobe was more than ample and the safe was very handy. The bathroom was incredibly clean, with a separate shower and bath and the toilet and bidet even had doors and a toilet!We ate at most of the restaurants with Panini being our favourite – it had a really relaxed cosmopolitan atmosphere. The food was great and the desserts were out of this world – it was so hard to choose and then there was a fantastic ice cream selection as well. Andiamo was beautifully designed and the food was delicious. We treated ourselves to a meal at the Manhattan Grill and yes it is expensive but worth every penny. The staff couldn’t do enough for us and the steaks were so tender and juicy – even mine which was well done. Again, the atmosphere was perfect and you could so easily have been in New York. Room service was surprisingly cheap and during Ramadan was a great option – it was always quick and the food was always hot.  The hotel is in a great location, a 10 minute transfer from the airport and there’s a free shuttle to the Wafi Mall which is just around the corner and is well worth a look – I got 40% off a Radley bag in the Radley bag shop and due to the strength of the pound against the Dhiram it was a snip! It was only a 15 minute ride to the Mall of the Emirates, we got a taxi from the lobby and it was no more expensive than a ‘normal’ taxi in Dubai. The lobby staff were always attentive and helpful – opening doors and carrying your shopping inside. We could not fault the friendliness or helpfulness of the staff. The hotel was amazingly clean and wherever you went staff were always cleaning or tidying but always had time to stop and say hello. There is an Arabian Adventures tour desk in the Lobby which we booked the Desert Safari and the Hatta Mountain Trek– they are a little pricier than the other companies but worth the extra money. We booked one tour through Alpha Tours which was enjoyable but not as well organised or value for money as Arabian.The pool complex was huge and the landscaping made you forget you were in the middle of a city. Our favourite pool was in a beach style and with a huge awning above the loungers meant we could duck out of the sun – which believe me was a god send. Sadly, we didn’t get a chance to use the spa or the gym but both looked impressive. This really is a 5* hotel – the service, the staff, the food the grounds. There’s even a Toni and Guy salon and several other little boutique shops. There were families, businessmen, travellers, couples and people travelling on their own from all the over world so it was a real mix of people. We would thoroughly recommend this hotel to anyone looking for an out of this world experience and for real luxury and pampering. We shall be returning next year!!	
