Aug 21 2007 	Fantastic Hotel if you have kids	We stayed for 2 weeks in January, with our 1 year old. It's a luxury hotel that isn't over run with children, but has all the facilities for them. The outdoor childrens pools are the best I have seen. The toddler pool is sloped like a beach, has a rubber non-slip floor, with the sunbed area partially covered with a shade sail. Our daughter lived in it, although rarely had to share it with more than 1 other child. The next level of pool has a great looking slide and a large meccano type structure in the middle, with valves to turn the water on and off. We look forward to our daughter trying it out next year!There are a number of good quality restraurants within the hotel . The Italian restaurant made a risotto specially for our daughter for free! The hotel will supply baby sitters - typically from the housekeeping staff. We found them to be really friendly.I have stayed in a number of Dubai hotels, and I rate this one the best when travelling with a child.	
