Mar 16 2007	Excellent trip to Dubai	We stayed at the Grand Hyatt Dubai from 10-14 March 2007. About a 10 minute taxi ride from the airport, but can't hear any aeroplane traffic from the rooms. Very friendly greeting on arrival and our bags were whisked away by the bellboys. Impressive entrance hall - very grand - but personally felt a little dated but only a minor comment. Lots of desks so we were able to check-in immediately and were offered a choice of twin or king room. I must say all of the staff were so friendly and couldn't do enough for you during our stay.We had a standard creekside king room. The room was very big, floor to ceiling windows, lounge chair, desk, and the biggest bathroom in any hotel I've stayed in. Fabulous walk in shower with good water pressure. Good maid service, frequent towel changes. We had to keep turning the aircon off as the room always so cold. Breakfast was 110 dirhams (about £15). Very good selection of hot and cold food, and as ever, efficient and friendly service.We had dinner in the Manhattan Grill. Modern, contemporary restaurant with a varied menu of meat and fish. Unfortunately our friend had to send her liver back which was raw and stringy. She chose something else and was not charged for the liver. Very expensive wine list, chose with caution! I also had lunch in Wox, the noodle bar, which was superb. The best noodles I've ever eaten, and only about £10. Another friend recommended Peppercrab, but we ran out of time, and the indian looked good, but again no time. There is also sushi, italian and lebanese.The bar Cooz off the reception is definitely worth a visit - dark, lit by candles, with comfy chairs, two gin &amp; tonics came in about £10, pretty reasonable. The outside areas are beautfiul. Gardens, streams, and a great pool. The sunbeds were the most comfortable I've ever sat on, and some have tents over the top, but these seemed to get snapped up early. The pool guys are so helpful and you really can't lift a finger - they adjust parasols, bring round cold towels, and food and drinks are waiter service all day. Heavenly! The pool area was really quiet when I was there. There is also a shallow children's pool covered by a canopy, and a large children's pool with slides/climbing frames etc. I tried the spa and had a pedicure , 230 dirhams (about £32) for 60 minutes. The indoor pool is lovely, and there is a big gym which was fairly busy. Overall, we loved this hotel and would go again, but I would personally prefer to be closer to Jumeirah beach (15 mins by taxi in clear traffic). The Madinat complex next to the Burj Al Arab / Wild Wadi Water park is just stunning, but more expensive. You can't have everything I guess ! Happy holidays.	
