Feb 24 2007	Exceptional Dining Experiences - every night!	Spent a week in Dubai with family. We were lucky enough to stay with them, so didn't need to worry about hotel accommodation. However I simply had to write a review about the standard of the various restaurants at The Grand Hyatt. From the moment we stepped into the lobby of this exceptional 5 star hotel, everything had the &quot;wow&quot; factor! On our first night of the holiday, we ate at &quot;Awtar&quot; - serving Arabian and Lebanese cuisine. We had the mezze meal. What a fantastic introduction to the country! We had about 10 cold starters (amazing Baba Ganoush, Fatoush, hummus etc), then came the hot starters, followed by main meal (baby octupus, various kebabs &amp; meats all chargrilled), finished with awesome dessert selection &amp; fruit bowl. Live traditional music &amp; belly dancing to accompany our meal. The second night we ate at The Sushi Bar - fantastic Japanese Sushi Chef. I've had Sushi in several places, but nothing could compare to this! The third night, we ate at Wox, serving Vietnamese food. The food here is very reasonably priced. Both chefs hail from Vietnam and we had a mouthwatering selection of traditional dishes. We had been to Vietnam before and the wonderful flavours brought back great memories of our time there. We took a break from the Grand Hyatt on the next night and we dined at The Thai Kitchen in the Park Hyatt. We opted for the set menu for 2 and a selection from the a la carte menu. Again - amazing! Our final night was spent at &quot;IZ&quot;, the new Indian restaurant at the Grand Hyatt. One can sit at the counter and watch the chefs at work - this is fun! Food was fantastic - especially the Cottage Cheese. The Passion Fruit Kulfi was memorable.. We had a light lunch at The Market Cafe one day - a huge selection of various cuisines to choose from. My son particularly loved the Chocolate Fountain for dessert.. :) The standards of genuine authentic food &amp; service at The Grand Hyatt are the best I've ever encountered on all my travels. Smiling happy faces greet you everywhere in the hotel. Genuine hospitality &amp; professionalism are apparent. I cannot recommend the food outlets of this fantastic hotel enough.	
